# Audio Engine Rules

## AudioContext
- Single shared AudioContext via getAudioContext() in engine.ts
- NEVER create AudioContext at module scope or import time
- Always call ensureAudioReady() before any audio operation
- Guard with typeof window !== 'undefined'

## smplr Integration
- All smplr imports must be dynamic: `const { SplendidGrandPiano } = await import('smplr')`
- Every instrument load must have try-catch with Soundfont fallback
- MAX_LOADED = 3 (LRU eviction)
- CacheStorage for repeat loads (HTTPS only)

## Unified Player
- playUnifiedChord/Bass/Melody routes through activeInstrumentId
- synth-fallback uses Tone.js, all others use smplr
- Velocity: smplr 0-127, Tone.js 0-1 (convert accordingly)
